67
00:03:57,671 --> 00:04:02,075 line:-2
Now, let's have a quick reminder
about the different rendering modes.


68
00:04:02,109 --> 00:04:04,778 line:-1
As you may know, in SF Symbols,


69
00:04:04.811 --> 00:04:07.047 line:-2 align:center
there are four rendering modes
to choose from,


70
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:12,519 line:-2
each one providing a greater control
over how color is applied to a symbol.


71
00:04:12,553 --> 00:04:16,323 line:-2
Monochrome is the most neutral
of all the rendering modes.


72
00:04:16,356 --> 00:04:18,825 line:-1
It gives a uniform and consistent look,


73
00:04:18,859 --> 00:04:21,428 line:-2
and it is the rendering mode
that most closely reflects


74
00:04:21,461 --> 00:04:24,965 line:-1
the typographic nature of SF Symbols.


75
00:04:24,998 --> 00:04:28,936 line:-2
Hierarchical is the rendering mode
that provides a subtle emphasis


76
00:04:28.969 --> 00:04:32.606 line:-2 align:center
while having a single color hue
drive the overall aesthetic.


77
00:04:32.639 --> 00:04:37.177 line:-2 align:center
We can apply depth by highlighting
the most important shape of a symbol


78
00:04:37.211 --> 00:04:40.981 line:-2 align:center
or differentiate the foreground
and background elements.


79
00:04:41,014 --> 00:04:44,618 line:-2
That way, we create a visual hierarchy
by emphasizing


80
00:04:44.651 --> 00:04:48.589 line:-1 align:center
the essential part or parts of a symbol.


81
00:04:48,622 --> 00:04:52,893 line:-2
Palette uses two or more contrasting
colors to give elements of a symbol


82
00:04:52,926 --> 00:04:54,895 line:-1
more prominence and versatility,


83
00:04:54,928 --> 00:04:57,598 line:-1
allowing for the symbols to be customized


84
00:04:57,631 --> 00:05:01,468 line:-2
to integrate with the color palette
of the environment.


85
00:05:01.502 --> 00:05:05.172 line:-2 align:center
Palette helps the symbols
have a contrasting and unique look


86
00:05:05,205 --> 00:05:08,809 line:-1
without sacrificing the overall aesthetic.


87
00:05:08.842 --> 00:05:12.779 line:-2 align:center
And Multicolor is the rendering mode
that represents the intrinsic


88
00:05:12,813 --> 00:05:15,249 line:-1
or native color of a symbol.


89
00:05:15,282 --> 00:05:19,753 line:-2
This rendering mode uses a range of colors
that can be applied to a symbol


90
00:05:19,786 --> 00:05:23,390 line:-2
to describe the appearance of an object
in the physical world,


91
00:05:23,423 --> 00:05:25,692 line:-2
or it can use colors
to emphasize the meaning


92
00:05:25,726 --> 00:05:28,061 line:-1
that the symbol is trying to convey.


93
00:05:28.095 --> 00:05:32.432 line:-2 align:center
You can use Multicolor when
the symbols are very prominent in the UI,


94
00:05:32,466 --> 00:05:38,038 line:-2
as it will help create a color narrative
that will relate to the symbol forms.


95
00:05:38,071 --> 00:05:42,376 line:-2
Until now, if you didn't explicitly
specify a rendering mode,


96
00:05:42.409 --> 00:05:44.478 line:-1 align:center
you would get Monochrome by default.


97
00:05:44.511 --> 00:05:47.514 line:-2 align:center
But this year,
we've made it easier to display symbols


98
00:05:47.548 --> 00:05:52.419 line:-2 align:center
in a rendering mode that best highlights
each symbol's unique characteristics.


99
00:05:52,452 --> 00:05:54,888 line:-2
Symbols now feature
a preferred rendering mode,


100
00:05:54.922 --> 00:05:57.624 line:-1 align:center
which can vary between symbols.


101
00:05:57.658 --> 00:06:01.495 line:-2 align:center
And we call this behavior
Automatic Rendering.


102
00:06:01.528 --> 00:06:05.432 line:-2 align:center
When selected, it provides
the preferred rendering mode configuration


103
00:06:05,465 --> 00:06:09,903 line:-2
for each symbol
without having to specify it manually.


104
00:06:09,937 --> 00:06:12,639 line:-1
For example, when Automatic is selected,


105
00:06:12,673 --> 00:06:16,143 line:-2
the camera filters symbol
will opt into Hierarchical,


106
00:06:16.176 --> 00:06:20.514 line:-2 align:center
as it is the rendering mode that conveys
a more precise visual representation


107
00:06:20,547 --> 00:06:23,917 line:-2
by highlighting the opacities
that reference the translucency


108
00:06:23.951 --> 00:06:27.654 line:-1 align:center
of the physical camera lenses and filters.


109
00:06:27.688 --> 00:06:29.590 line:-1 align:center
Here's another example.


110
00:06:29,623 --> 00:06:31,692 line:-1
When Automatic is selected,


111
00:06:31.725 --> 00:06:36.263 line:-2 align:center
the SharePlay symbol participates
in the Hierarchical rendering mode.


112
00:06:36,296 --> 00:06:41,068 line:-2
This behavior lets the person's shape
stand prominently in the foreground


113
00:06:41,101 --> 00:06:44,838 line:-2
while the waves play a secondary role
in the background.


114
00:06:44.872 --> 00:06:48.108 line:-2 align:center
Again,
this emphasizes the symbol's concept,


115
00:06:48,141 --> 00:06:50,944 line:-2
as the SharePlay feature
is mainly a way to share


116
00:06:50.978 --> 00:06:53.981 line:-1 align:center
and connect with friends and family.


117
00:06:54,014 --> 00:06:57,918 line:-2
In most cases,
Automatic will be the best way to go.


118
00:06:57.951 --> 00:07:00.587 line:-2 align:center
But you always have to be aware
of the context.


119
00:07:00.621 --> 00:07:05.526 line:-2 align:center
For example, the AirPods Pro symbol
will render as Hierarchical


120
00:07:05,559 --> 00:07:07,561 line:-1
when Automatic is selected.


121
00:07:07,594 --> 00:07:10,731 line:-2
But in this context,
the symbol is very small


122
00:07:10,764 --> 00:07:15,502 line:-2
and has low contrast
when presented on this background.


123
00:07:15.536 --> 00:07:19.606 line:-2 align:center
Remember that rendering modes
can still be explicitly specified


124
00:07:19.640 --> 00:07:24.678 line:-2 align:center
for a uniform appearance
across symbols in a particular context.


125
00:07:24.711 --> 00:07:28.215 line:-2 align:center
So in this case,
Monochrome will be the best choice


126
00:07:28.248 --> 00:07:33.053 line:-2 align:center
as it is more legible
and has fewer details at small sizes.


127
00:07:33,086 --> 00:07:38,959 line:-2
So always make sure to specify the most
suitable rendering mode configuration.


128
00:07:38.992 --> 00:07:42.529 line:-2 align:center
The different rendering modes
apply color to symbols


129
00:07:42.563 --> 00:07:46.900 line:-2 align:center
to present visual solutions
for a wide range of circumstances.


130
00:07:46,934 --> 00:07:51,438 line:-2
Color is a powerful tool,
and we can explore it even further.


131
00:07:51.471 --> 00:07:54.141 line:-1 align:center
Some symbols are more dynamic in nature.


132
00:07:54.174 --> 00:07:56.910 line:-1 align:center
If we analyze their visual representation,


133
00:07:56.944 --> 00:07:59.780 line:-1 align:center
we can notice two main characteristics:


134
00:07:59.813 --> 00:08:05.385 line:-2 align:center
first, their paths or shapes convey
varying levels of strength,


135
00:08:05.419 --> 00:08:08.422 line:-2 align:center
and second,
they rely on color to communicate


136
00:08:08,455 --> 00:08:11,625 line:-1
their status changing over time.


137
00:08:11,658 --> 00:08:14,361 line:-2
This year,
we're expanding the use of color


138
00:08:14,394 --> 00:08:18,432 line:-2
by introducing a new feature
called Variable Color.


139
00:08:18,465 --> 00:08:22,202 line:-2
We've arranged the symbol's vector paths
into layers


140
00:08:22,236 --> 00:08:25,606 line:-2
and organized those layers
in sequential order,


141
00:08:25.639 --> 00:08:29.576 line:-2 align:center
creating a new method of
distributing color through these layers.


142
00:08:29,610 --> 00:08:32,579 line:-2
This allows us
to convey different levels of strength


143
00:08:32,613 --> 00:08:34,882 line:-1
or communicate a sequence over time,


144
00:08:34,915 --> 00:08:38,952 line:-2
which is dictated by the nature
of the design of the symbol.


145
00:08:38,986 --> 00:08:42,256 line:-2
One important thing to know is that,
in Variable Color,


146
00:08:42,289 --> 00:08:46,159 line:-2
some symbols have all paths
participating in the sequence,


147
00:08:46,193 --> 00:08:51,565 line:-2
but for other symbols,
only some of the paths may opt-in.


148
00:08:51.598 --> 00:08:54.601 line:-1 align:center
Let's look at a few examples.


149
00:08:54,635 --> 00:08:58,772 line:-2
With Variable Color,
we want the paths representing the iPhone


150
00:08:58,805 --> 00:09:01,408 line:-1
to opt-out of the variable sequence,


151
00:09:01,441 --> 00:09:05,445 line:-2
and we want to highlight the paths
representing the radio waves.


152
00:09:05.479 --> 00:09:09.917 line:-2 align:center
This will help differentiate the stages
that describe the levels of strength


153
00:09:09.950 --> 00:09:12.920 line:-1 align:center
of the radio signal of the phone.


154
00:09:12,953 --> 00:09:16,924 line:-2
It's important to know that we define
how we want to group the paths.


155
00:09:16.957 --> 00:09:19.359 line:-2 align:center
For example,
it wouldn't make much sense


156
00:09:19,393 --> 00:09:23,030 line:-2
to highlight the waves
from left to right in this case.


157
00:09:23,063 --> 00:09:26,767 line:-2
So instead, we can group the paths
following the sequence


158
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:30,170 line:-2
that best conveys
the radio signal strength:


159
00:09:30,204 --> 00:09:33,440 line:-2
we have the two smaller waves
in one layer,


160
00:09:33,473 --> 00:09:36,743 line:-2
and we have the two bigger waves
in a different layer.


161
00:09:36.777 --> 00:09:41.915 line:-2 align:center
And as mentioned, the phone does
not participate in the variable sequence.


162
00:09:41,949 --> 00:09:46,486 line:-2
This time, let's look at a symbol
that we are very familiar with.


163
00:09:46.520 --> 00:09:50.691 line:-2 align:center
In most cases, this symbol is paired
with a built-in slider


164
00:09:50,724 --> 00:09:54,695 line:-2
that syncs with the states
represented in the symbol.


165
00:09:54,728 --> 00:09:57,631 line:-2
The waves highlight their paths
following a sequence


166
00:09:57.664 --> 00:10:00.434 line:-2 align:center
dictated by the user
controlling the slider,


167
00:10:00.467 --> 00:10:04.505 line:-1 align:center
increasing or decreasing the volume level.


168
00:10:04,538 --> 00:10:06,340 line:-1
Like in the iPhone example,


169
00:10:06,373 --> 00:10:09,710 line:-2
we have a path that doesn't participate
in the sequence,


170
00:10:09,743 --> 00:10:12,546 line:-2
which is the shape illustrating
the speaker,


171
00:10:12.579 --> 00:10:15.883 line:-2 align:center
and we have paths
that do participate in the sequence,


172
00:10:15,916 --> 00:10:19,820 line:-2
which are the three waves
that define the volume's strength:


173
00:10:19,853 --> 00:10:24,191 line:-2
low volume, mid-volume,
and high volume.


174
00:10:24,224 --> 00:10:27,027 line:-1
These paths are organized into layers,


175
00:10:27,060 --> 00:10:32,065 line:-2
and the selected layers opt-in
to the Variable Color feature.


176
00:10:32.099 --> 00:10:35.936 line:-2 align:center
We represent their strength
with percentage values:


177
00:10:35,969 --> 00:10:38,105 line:0
0% is entirely off,


178
00:10:38,138 --> 00:10:42,376 align:center
anything above 0%
will highlight part of the symbol,


179
00:10:42,409 --> 00:10:48,582 line:0
and the whole symbol will be fully
highlighted as the value approaches 100%.


180
00:10:48.615 --> 00:10:51.385 line:-2 align:center
One important thing to know
is that Variable Color


181
00:10:51,418 --> 00:10:53,654 line:-1
is not meant to create depth;


182
00:10:53.687 --> 00:10:58.125 line:-2 align:center
instead, it's meant to highlight
a sequence of steps or stages


183
00:10:58.158 --> 00:11:00.561 line:-1 align:center
that the symbol can represent.


184
00:11:00.594 --> 00:11:03.497 line:-2 align:center
For example,
let's imagine I need a symbol


185
00:11:03.530 --> 00:11:06.366 line:-2 align:center
to represent people's capacity
inside a room.


186
00:11:06.400 --> 00:11:08.969 line:-1 align:center
This symbol looks great for that.


187
00:11:09.002 --> 00:11:11.638 line:-1 align:center
Let's look at it in more detail.


188
00:11:11,672 --> 00:11:15,275 line:-2
We don't want to highlight
just one part of the symbol.


189
00:11:15.309 --> 00:11:20.747 line:-2 align:center
Instead, we need to think of the symbol
as a sequence or a range.


190
00:11:20.781 --> 00:11:23.283 line:-1 align:center
My goal is to cover different states:


191
00:11:23.317 --> 00:11:25.352 line:-1 align:center
the room is empty,


192
00:11:25,385 --> 00:11:28,222 line:-1
the room has few people in it,


193
00:11:28,255 --> 00:11:32,659 line:-2
the room is half-full,
and the room is at full capacity.


194
00:11:32.693 --> 00:11:36.129 line:-1 align:center
So now, when I opt into Variable Color,


195
00:11:36.163 --> 00:11:38.699 line:-2 align:center
I can easily see
the graphic representation


196
00:11:38,732 --> 00:11:41,602 line:-2
of the different states
I'm trying to convey.


197
00:11:41.635 --> 00:11:45.772 line:-2 align:center
And there are no limits to how
many paths can opt into the feature.


198
00:11:45,806 --> 00:11:48,008 line:-1
There can be just one or many.


199
00:11:48.041 --> 00:11:52.012 line:-2 align:center
You decide what is the design strategy
that best suits your needs.


200
00:11:52,045 --> 00:11:56,617 line:-2
If you want to represent the strength
level of shapes that follow a sequence,


201
00:11:56,650 --> 00:11:59,920 line:-1
like waves, rays, ellipsis, and layers,


202
00:11:59,953 --> 00:12:02,890 line:-1
you can do so with Variable Color.


203
00:12:02.923 --> 00:12:07.561 line:-2 align:center
Variable Color is opacity based
and it's available in all rendering modes.


204
00:12:09,029 --> 00:12:14,168 line:-2
This year, we have made annotations for
custom symbols faster and easier to use


205
00:12:14.201 --> 00:12:18.705 line:-2 align:center
by creating a unified layer
structure across all rendering modes.


206
00:12:18,739 --> 00:12:21,775 line:-2
I love baking,
and I was thinking of designing an app


207
00:12:21,808 --> 00:12:23,977 line:-1
with cupcake-only recipes.


208
00:12:24,011 --> 00:12:26,713 line:-1
I wanted to create my own custom symbols,


209
00:12:26.747 --> 00:12:29.683 line:-2 align:center
