212
00:12:36,023 --> 00:12:40,194 line:-2
and how to annotate symbols
that participate in Variable Color.


213
00:12:40,227 --> 00:12:43,197 line:-1
Let's use these two as an example.


214
00:12:43,230 --> 00:12:47,134 line:-2
Before we start annotating,
there are a few things to consider:


215
00:12:47.167 --> 00:12:52.472 line:-2 align:center
we need to keep the hierarchy in mind
and make sure we outline the z-order.


216
00:12:52,506 --> 00:12:58,545 line:0
The z-order refers to the order
of the paths in a symbol along the z-axis.


217
00:12:58,579 --> 00:13:02,583 line:0
There are also two new concepts
you need to be aware of:


218
00:13:02.616 --> 00:13:05.085 line:-1 align:center
Draw and Erase.


219
00:13:05.118 --> 00:13:08.989 line:-2 align:center
These are used to help define the way
a layer renders.


220
00:13:09.022 --> 00:13:12.559 line:-2 align:center
For example,
here we have the paths of a symbol


221
00:13:12,593 --> 00:13:16,163 line:-2
representing a square
overlapping a circle.


222
00:13:16.196 --> 00:13:19.066 line:-2 align:center
When selecting the layers
containing the square,


223
00:13:19.099 --> 00:13:21.068 line:-1 align:center
if we choose the Draw option,


224
00:13:21.101 --> 00:13:24.638 line:-2 align:center
the layer will draw the paths
contained in that layer.


225
00:13:24,671 --> 00:13:26,974 line:-1
If we choose the Erase option,


226
00:13:27,007 --> 00:13:30,310 line:-2
the layer will erase the path
containing the layer,


227
00:13:30,344 --> 00:13:33,347 line:-1
affecting how the symbol is rendered.


228
00:13:33,380 --> 00:13:36,149 line:-1
Now, let's start annotating the cupcake.


229
00:13:36.183 --> 00:13:39.953 line:-2 align:center
As a first step, we need to organize
the paths in layers


230
00:13:39,987 --> 00:13:42,723 line:-1
to create the desired hierarchy.


231
00:13:42,756 --> 00:13:47,361 line:-2
If I analyze it closely,
I can see four main shapes:


232
00:13:47.394 --> 00:13:50.564 line:-1 align:center
the frosting, the cupcake base,


233
00:13:50,597 --> 00:13:53,033 line:-1
the badge, and the plus.


234
00:13:53,066 --> 00:13:56,403 line:-2
You can add as many paths as needed
to a layer.


235
00:13:56.436 --> 00:13:59.773 line:-2 align:center
So in this case,
the frosting will be defined


236
00:13:59.806 --> 00:14:02.476 line:-1 align:center
by a layer with three different paths,


237
00:14:02,509 --> 00:14:07,447 line:-2
and the rest of the layers will be defined
by just one path each.


238
00:14:07,481 --> 00:14:12,085 line:-2
Organizing the shapes in this way
allows us to have more flexibility


239
00:14:12,119 --> 00:14:15,722 line:-2
when annotating one structure
for all rendering modes.


240
00:14:15,756 --> 00:14:18,892 line:-2
Now we have all the information
we need in one place


241
00:14:18,926 --> 00:14:21,428 line:-1
to customize the symbol as needed.


242
00:14:22,396 --> 00:14:26,166 line:-2
Now we can start annotating
all rendering modes.


243
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:28,735 line:-1
Let's look at Multicolor first.


244
00:14:28.769 --> 00:14:31.038 line:-1 align:center
I already have the shapes set up,


245
00:14:31.071 --> 00:14:33.774 line:-1 align:center
so I just need to choose the right colors.


246
00:14:33,807 --> 00:14:36,210 line:-1
Red Velvet is my favorite flavor,


247
00:14:36,243 --> 00:14:41,215 line:-2
so I'll choose white for the frosting
and red for the cupcake base.


248
00:14:41,248 --> 00:14:44,818 line:-2
Now I will follow the same logic
that SF Symbols defines


249
00:14:44.852 --> 00:14:47.554 line:-1 align:center
for the plus badges in Multicolor:


250
00:14:47,588 --> 00:14:50,824 line:-2
green for the badge
and white for the plus.


251
00:14:50,858 --> 00:14:54,294 line:-1
Okay, this is looking great so far.


252
00:14:54,328 --> 00:14:56,296 line:-1
Now, let's focus on the badge.


253
00:14:56,330 --> 00:15:00,834 line:-2
This is where the unified annotation
approach is more apparent.


254
00:15:00,868 --> 00:15:03,203 line:-1
We already defined Multicolor.


255
00:15:03.237 --> 00:15:06.406 line:-2 align:center
Now let's look at Hierarchical
and Palette.


256
00:15:06.440 --> 00:15:09.843 line:-2 align:center
Because of the use of hierarchy
in this rendering modes,


257
00:15:09.877 --> 00:15:12.379 line:-1 align:center
I would expect the badge to be Primary,


258
00:15:12.412 --> 00:15:17.217 line:-2 align:center
which will render it white
on a black background, like this one.


259
00:15:17,251 --> 00:15:21,355 line:-2
Now I need the plus shape
to erase part of the badge.


260
00:15:21,388 --> 00:15:24,224 line:-2
This is where the Erase selection
is helpful.


261
00:15:24,258 --> 00:15:27,394 line:-2
I will be able to see the badge
rendered as desired


262
00:15:27,427 --> 00:15:32,566 line:-2
by erasing a part of a shape
when the layers overlap.


263
00:15:32,599 --> 00:15:36,170 line:-2
Finally, I just need
the Monochrome annotation.


264
00:15:36,203 --> 00:15:39,406 line:-2
Because there is no added complexity
in this rendering mode,


265
00:15:39,439 --> 00:15:41,308 line:-1
I will follow the same logic,


266
00:15:41,341 --> 00:15:46,213 line:-2
making the plus shape
erase part of the badge shape.


267
00:15:46,246 --> 00:15:48,115 line:-1
I'm almost done now.


268
00:15:48.148 --> 00:15:50.918 line:-1 align:center
I just need a few extra details.


269
00:15:50,951 --> 00:15:53,987 line:-2
For Hierarchical and Palette,
I just need to annotate


270
00:15:54.021 --> 00:15:57.191 line:-2 align:center
the rest of the cupcake shape
as Secondary.


271
00:15:57.224 --> 00:16:01.528 line:-2 align:center
For Palette, I will choose a color
to give a bit of contrast.


272
00:16:01,562 --> 00:16:04,364 line:-2
And for Monochrome,
I just need to make sure


273
00:16:04.398 --> 00:16:07.668 line:-2 align:center
I have the remaining shapes
opting into Draw.


274
00:16:09,503 --> 00:16:11,038 line:-1
That's all I need.


275
00:16:11,071 --> 00:16:14,942 line:-2
The cupcake is ready and customized
for all rendering modes.


276
00:16:16,777 --> 00:16:19,213 line:-1
Now let's look at the kitchen timer.


277
00:16:19,246 --> 00:16:23,217 line:-2
The paths represent the time passing,
and since this is a sequence,


278
00:16:23.250 --> 00:16:27.221 line:-2 align:center
